  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 190°C (375°F).",
    "Grease a bamboo tray with butter.",
    "Layer the cured pork belly slices and bacon evenly in the tray.",
    "Sprinkle minced garlic, chopped thyme, lemon zest, salt, and pepper over the meat.",
    "Pour the heavy cream evenly over the pork layers.",
    "Sprinkle shredded Gruyere and grated Parmesan cheese on top.",
    "Bake in the preheated oven for 35 minutes until the top is golden and crispy.",
    "Let the gratin rest for 5 minutes before serving."
